{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χέρσος</b>, <br /> later <i>Attic dialect</i> <b>χέρρος</b>, ἡ, <b>dry land,</b> opposed to water, ἐπὶ χέρσου, opposed to ἐν πόντῳ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.459, compare 15.495; κύματα μακρὰ κυλινδόμενα προτὶ χέρσον 9.147; λάϊγγας ποτὶ χ. ἀποπλύνεσκε θάλασσα 6.95; κῦμα.. βοάᾳ ποτὶ χ. 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.394; κῦμα.. χέρσῳ ῥηγνύμενον μεγάλα βρέμει 4.425; χέρσον ἱκέσθαι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.486, 542; ἐπὶ χέρσω 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica “Papyrus fragments” in E. Diehl, 9.10; κατὰ χέρσον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 873 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 884 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χέρσῳ <b>on</b> or <b>by land,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 977 (Lyric poetry), “Ag.” 558, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 1066: proverbial, ἐν πόντῳ νᾶες, ἐνχέρσῳ πόλεμοι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 12.4, compare “N.” 1.62; πολλὰ.. ἐκ θαλάσσης, πολλὰ δ᾽ ἐκ χέρσου κακὰ γίγνεται 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 707 (troch.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πάνδοκον εἰς ἀφανῆ τε χ., of the realm of Hades, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Th.” 860 (Lyric poetry).—In 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] the gender cannot be determined, <i>feminine</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 75.17 (uncertain reading), 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 31 (_anapaest meter_), 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 3.13.3, 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 3.15, etc.: _plural_, ἐν ταῖς χέρσοις\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] on <b>barren soils,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 8.6.4. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] as <i>adjective</i>, χέρσος, ον, <b>dry, firm,</b> of land, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.99 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; Εὐρώπαν ποτὶ χέρσον to <b>the mainland</b> of Europe, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 4.70; ἐν κονίᾳ χέρσῳ, opposed to πόντῳ, [prev. work] 9.43. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>dry, hard, barren,</b> τῆς χώρης ἐούσης χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.123; στύφλος δὲ γῆ καὶ χ. 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 251 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; παραδοῦναι [τὴν γῆν] χέρρον, i.e. ψιλήν, <b>without a crop</b> on it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.2492.16; χ. καὶ ἄκανθα ἔσται ἡ γῆ LXX.Isa.7.24; χέρσα \">LXX</a>]<b>waste places,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 189 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χ. λιμήν a harbour <b>left dry,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 9.427 (6th c.AD: Barbucallos Epigrammaticus): frequently in Papyrus, “PAmh.” 2.31.12 (2nd c.BC), etc. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>barren,</b> of women, χέρσους φθαρῆναι κἀγάμους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1502. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.3.b</b></Level4> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>barren of,</b> πυρὰ χέρσος ἀγλαϊς μάτων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 325 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Sanskrit <i>hár[snull]ate</i> 'become stiff, bristle', Avest. <b>zarštva-</b> 'stone', Latin <i>horreo.</i>)","strongNumber":"G9719","accentedUnicode":"χέρσος","shortDef":"uncultivated","mediumDef":"uncultivated","stepGloss":"uncultivated","stepTransliteration":"chersos","_step_Type":"word"}]}